Product Description

A Large Screen at Home with UGREEN HDMI to DVI Cable!

UGREEN High-Speed HDMI to DVI-I (24+5) Adapter Cable allows you to connect your HDMI-equipped source devices such as Blu-Ray, Xbox 360, PS3, Apple TV, DVD, and Set Top Box to your DVI-enabled HDTV, Displays, Projectors and more. Moreover, you can also use it to connect DVI source devices, like laptop/ desktop to HDTV and displays with HDMI interface at high definition. Suitable for a conference, video, education, and gaming, enjoy an external display easily.

Stable Transmission, Bi-directional Connection

Aluminum foil shielding + braid shielding + ground line, triple-shield protection, thicken tinned copper core, offer you a more stable signal transmission. And the PVC jacket makes it softer and more flexible. Supported two way converter: DVI to HDMI and HDMI to DVI.

Two Modes Freely Switch

Extended mode: Two screens show the different content. One for work, another for entertainment.

Cloned mode: Two screens show the same image. Enjoy the movies or play games on HDTV, which displays the same content as your computer desktop.

Specification

Fully compatible with all HDTV formats. Supports resolution up to 1080p

Triple shielding and gold-plated connectors that resist corrosion while offering optimum signal transfer

Support transfer of uncompressed high-definition video

24k Gold-Plated Connectors for more insertion and extraction.

30AWG Oxygen-free copper for less signal loss transfer

Triple-layer superior shielding for protection against electromagnetic interference (EMI) and radio frequency interference (RFI)

Please Note DVI port does not support audio output, so a separated audio cable is needed for sound transmission from HDMI to DVI display monitor.

HDMI to DVI 24+5 HDMI to DVI 24+1 Bi-directional HDMI to 24+1 Bi-directional HDMI to VGA
Cable length 15cm 1M / 2M / 3M / 5M 15cm 15cm
Resolution 1080P 1080P 1080P 1080P
Bi-directional X

      How are ratings calculated?
      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzes reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      5.0 out of 5 stars Fixed old Wacom tablet connection issue
      Reviewed in the United States on March 22, 2019
      Verified Purchase
      I have a older Wacom 21UX pen tablet/monitor that has an analog/ digital DVI-I connector that doesn't physically fit in more modern digital-only DVI connectors, like those on all recent video cards. In desperation I bought this DVI-I to HDMI dongle hoping it would work. It did! I had to call Wacom customer support and go back to a much earlier tablet driver to get everything working, but everything is good! (Uninstall latest driver, unplug USB, install older driver, then plug USB back in...the blue light comes on and it is a tablet again!) The DVI-I to HDMI just feeds video signal and the USB is what enables the tablet functions. It works, it was here quickly, and reasonably priced.
